## 3\. Deployment Steps

Follow these steps to deploy the script:

1. Save the project by clicking the disk icon.  
2. Replace 'YOUR\_FOLDER\_ID\_HERE' with the actual ID of your target folder (found in the URL when you open the folder in Google Drive).  
3. Delete any existing code in the editor and paste the code provided above.  
4. Navigate to Extensions \> Apps Script.  
5. Open your Google Sheet or create a new one.

## 4\. How to Run

To execute the script:

1. Click Allow.  
2. The first time you run this, you will be prompted to Review Permissions. Click Review Permissions, select your account, click Advanced, and then click Go to (Script Name) (unsafe).  
3. Click the Run button.  
4. In the Apps Script editor, ensure the function runAutoReconstruction is selected in the toolbar.

## 5\. How to Monitor Progress

1. Logger: The script uses Logger.log(). You can view these outputs in the execution details to track specific steps.  
2. Live Updates: You can filter by the date/time to see the status (Completed, Failed, or Running).  
3. Execution Logs: Click on the Executions tab in the left-hand sidebar of the Apps Script interface.

## 6\. What to Expect After Execution

1. Notifications: If email triggers are set up, you will receive a summary notification.  
2. File Changes: Depending on the script logic, you should see new files generated in your target directory.  
3. Confirmation: If successful, you will see a “Reconstruction completed successfully” entry in the logs.

## 7\. Troubleshooting

1. Timeout: If the script runs for more than 6 minutes, Apps Script might time out. You may need to optimize the script to process items in smaller batches.  
2. Invalid ID: Double-check that your Folder ID is correct and is not a link or sharing URL.  
3. Permission Denied: Ensure your Google account has Editor access to the specific folder.

## 8\. Post-Execution Validation

Once the script has finished:

1. Logs Review: Verify there are no red “Failed” status indicators in the Executions tab.  
2. Sample Verification: Open 2-3 random files to ensure the data was populated/reconstructed correctly.  
3. Check File Counts: Verify that the number of files generated matches your expectations.